@test: Define a test method. This annotation is used to indicate that a method is a test method that should be executed by the testing framework.
@mock: Define a mock object. This annotation is used in testing to create a mock implementation of a class or interface, allowing you to simulate the behavior of dependencies in your tests.
@injectMock: Define a mock injection point. This annotation is used in testing to specify where a mock object should be injected into the class being tested.
@injectable: Define a class that can be injected into other classes. This is used for dependency injection.